SIMPLE: invulnerable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invulnerable
<hw>In*vul"ner*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>invulnerabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>invuln⟦eacute⟧rable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Vulnerable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Incapable of being wounded, or of receiving
injury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither vainly hope⟦br⟧
To be <qex>invulnerable</qex> in those bright arms.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unanswerable; irrefutable; that can not be refuted
or convinced; <as>as, an <ex>invulnerable</ex> argument</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invulnerableness</ent>⟦br⟧
